Reflecting on this year, it was the most challenging and emotionally draining for me. I’m proud of the woman I’ve become. I’ve learned so much about myself. I took time for my mental health. I found out what I want in this life, what I truly need. I stepped out of my comfort zone. I made decisions for myself and my happiness. I walked away from a 8 year relationship. I moved into my own home. Through the heartbreaks, the highs and lows, the emotional rollercoaster I’ve rode on… I’m finally happier than I’ve ever been. I’m at peace with who I am, and where I am. I’m so happy to put 2023 behind me. 2024 will be the best year yet… Happy New Year everyone🥳
